<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="962" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d962">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-08"><hi rend="italic">May 8,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 153.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch, No. 143, of March 1 last, on the subject of the abduction of
                            Miss Stone.</p>
                        <p>You will express the grateful appreciation of the Presidents and myself
                            to the persons mentioned in your dispatch for their generous and
                            valuable services in connection with the release of Miss Stone.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>